        "id": 5640
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-07-07T20:16:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My original plan had been to simply not have these accessors in Type at all, requiring you to cast Type to the subclass, as we do with Expression et al., so you\u0027d use type.as\u003cScalarType\u003e().priority().\n\nFor the time being I had simply left these accessors in place to reduce churn in this patch, intending to address the API changes in a followup. But upon further reflection, it\u0027s probably best to just stick with the existing API.",
      "parentUuid": "2350baf1_e043f8d9",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 85,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 94,
        "endChar": 1
      },
      "revId": "2329efae28ea0a3dc58002c9bc5458285c92cc43",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "35ce238f_b3263a20",
        "filename": "src/sksl/ir/SkSLType.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 94,
      "author": {
        "id": 11059
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-07-07T20:59:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Actually, an interesting middle ground might be to mark the Type subclasses as final, and expose them in SkSLType.h. Most callers can just say `type.priority()` and incur a virtual call. Callers who know the type subclass can say `type.as\u003cScalarType\u003e().priority()` instead and the compiler could potentially inline the call (since ScalarType is final, the compiler can know which `priority` function we mean).\n\nIn practice I doubt any of this is measurable, though. One virtual call is pretty cheap, unless we\u0027re doing an analysis pass or something and hitting every IRNode in a program in a tight loop. We can land the current CL as-is and poke around with it later (if we actually need to).",
      "parentUuid": "bf8e5d03_69c8a564",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 85,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 94,
        "endChar": 1
      },
      "revId": "2329efae28ea0a3dc58002c9bc5458285c92cc43",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
